{
  "stem": "26142.17",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They were about this wide, just enough for a person, you know, around 20, 24 inches to-- to-- maybe to turn around.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Four, three-- three-- three high, just like chicken coops.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But when we came in there, the-- the-- the-- it-- it-- it-- it smelled that it was fresh, clean.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was not-- not like in-- in-- in Flossenburg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The first thing, we-- we found the local-- the-- the-- the ones that were there were not as bitter as-- as the-- the-- the one in-- in-- in Flossenburg.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I remember the first ones that greeted us, they told us, that you-- you-- there is a-- they warned us about the kapo of-- of this block.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "That he is a terrible sadist, to watch out, to watch out not to get in trouble with him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But they were, more or less, friendly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they warned us do not drink the water, no matter how thirsty you are because there is something in the water that-- that there is dysentery, and people fall like flies after a few-- after a few weeks.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They said, if you-- if you feel like you're very thirsty, you-- you should take some snow.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You know, we had snow, already, that time, on the ground.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And in that-- and in that camp, the next-- the next day, they [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] didn't send us out to work.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They asked that we should select a-- a-- kapo from among our-- our people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I remember we had a Hungarian-Jewish boy by the name of [HUNGARIAN] that was very respected from all of us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And each-- when-- in-- he-- he was, so to speak, regarded as our-- our spokesman, the-- the leader under the Hungarian [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
